Thornwood is a necrotic estate-forest north of Midgaard occupying the transition belt between Midgaard's grave districts and Shadowmere's southern approach. Four governing logics operate simultaneously: manorial (gates, titles, hereditary protocols), funerary (barrows, charnel verges, bone-processing cycles), forest (root pressure, adaptive pathing, canopy suppression), and substrate (a pre-human crystalline geological formation beneath the estate that mediates the necrotic ecology and whose binding is currently failing). The pre-estate layer: burial woodland used by itinerant communities and ridge clans practicing face-down oathbreaker burials (interred facing down so they could not rise toward sky), thorn-ring containment growth (planted thorn rings functioning as sealed verdicts), and ritualized path detours around ancestor stands (dead governed those spaces, living had no right of passage). The Harren Charter established a fortified manor in exchange for timber extraction rights, hunting tithes, and burial lease fees — creating a secondary burial site privately administered but nominally subject to civic audit. When grave labor accumulated around the burial operations, the Root Covenant cult emerged among estate laborers who reinterpreted the pre-estate burial customs as doctrine. The Wild Hunt is Thornwood's mobile enforcement arm, currently patrolling farther toward the Lantern Road's southern approaches than in any prior generation as the substrate crystal binding fails. Thornwood is carved out from normal warden jurisdiction — the iron gate connects into a grave tunnel system older than either Thornwood or Shadowmere, which both Midgaard and Shadowmere's garrison use for supply and intelligence routing. Neither city will seal Thornwood because doing so would require closing a transit passage both need.

