Midgaard's relationship to Thornwood is defined by administrative carve-out and strategic avoidance. The Harren Charter was a standard frontier expansion instrument; the burial lease provision created a privately administered interment site that Sepulchur Pasture was meant to audit but never consistently did. The Root Covenant cult's emergence and its exploitation of the substrate crystal formation was not detected until the Wild Hunt began extending its patrol range. Warden cartographers mark Thornwood with a non-standard hazard sigil; convoy writs treat its perimeter as a legal exception area. The carve-out is politically convenient: both Midgaard and Kowloon acknowledge Thornwood as real while denying full jurisdictional responsibility. Ninth Acre records in Sepulchur Pasture lore include identity-stripped casualties from woodland incidents — a paper trail connecting Thornwood events to Midgaard mortality records even though no warden is assigned to monitor Thornwood directly.

