Rivennid ecological analysis of Thornwood identifies the substrate crystal formation as the critical variable: a geological anomaly responsive to biological activity above it, possibly connected to the same pre-human construction tradition attested by worked stone fragments at Midgaard's Watchers' Cairn site. The Rivennid concern is not the necrotic ecology per se but the substrate's capacity to fuse the manorial, funerary, and forest logics into a single operating system that treats death as raw material rather than as part of regeneration. The Great Northern Forest's root network does not extend into Thornwood; the carve-out from normal warden jurisdiction is an ecological carve-out as well. Rivennid in Midgaard working on Lantern Road ecology assessments track the Wild Hunt's patrol expansion as an indicator of how far the substrate's influence is extending beyond the estate boundary.

